      "service": "S3 Presigned URLs (SigV4)",
      "note": "upload_handler.py and delete_handler.py explicitly configure boto3 S3 client with s3v4 signature_version and virtual addressing style. Azure equivalent: SAS tokens — different signature algorithm and URL structure. All clients consuming presigned URLs will need to handle the new SAS URL format."
    },
    {
      "service": "S3 Object Tagging",
      "note": "upload_handler.py sets x-amz-tagging on presigned POST. list_handler.py calls s3.get_object_tagging per object. Azure Blob Storage uses blob tags (GA) — functionally equivalent but API differs."
    },
    {
      "service": "S3 Object Metadata (x-amz-meta-*)",
      "note": "upload_handler.py stores uploaddate, originalfilename, and description as S3 custom metadata headers. list_handler.py and view_handler.py read these via head_object. Azure Blob Storage supports user-defined metadata with the same key-value model."
    },
    {
      "service": "AWS SigV4 (execute-api:Invoke)",
      "note": "API Gateway uses AWS_IAM auth on all resource methods. The frontend SPA authenticates using IAM user access keys (AKIAXZEFIIOD2OIWPRPK) and signs requests with SigV4. Azure equivalent: API Management with managed identity or OAuth2 — requires frontend auth refactor."
    },
    {
      "service": "CORS (S3 + API Gateway)",
      "note": "Both S3 ImageBucket and API Gateway resources have CORS configured. All four API routes have OPTIONS methods with MOCK integration for preflight. Azure equivalents need matching CORS configuration on Blob Storage and Azure Functions/APIM."
    }
  ]
